NOTES: A Berber student was shot while in police custody at a police station in Beni Douala. He later died on Apr.21.
Riots were reported in numerous villages in Kabylie, resulting in dozens wounded in clashes between protesters and police and significant material damage.
Students protested in the Amizour area. At least 3 were later arrested for allegedly insulting gendarmes.
Rioters threw molotov cocktails, rocks and burning tires at gendarmerie stations in Beni Douala, El-Kseur and Amizour.
